General Information
===================


This is ABACUS version 3.0 
ABACUS is a C++ class library for
the implementation of Branch-and-Cut-and-Price algorithms. 

The official web site is:
  http://www.informatik.uni-koeln.de/abacus

The official mailing list:

The mailing list is a forum for ABACUS related discussions of any
kind. In order to subscribe please visit the url:

https://lists.uni-koeln.de/mailman/listinfo/abacus-forum


Installation & Dependencies
===========================

See the file 'INSTALL'


How to report bugs
==================

Bugs should be reported to abacus@informatik.uni-koeln.de

In the bug report please include:

* Information about your system. For instance:

   - What operating system and version
   - What compiler and version
   - What LP-solver
   - What coin-Osi version
   - For Linux, what version of the C library

  And anything else you think is relevant. For instance:

   - A log-file produced with log-level `Full'
   - A log-file produced with option PrintLP

* How to reproduce the bug. 

* If the bug was a crash, the exact text that was printed out
  when the crash occurred.

* Further information such as stack traces may be useful, but
  is not necessary.
